A fierce cyclone struck Bangladesh's coast, causing severe damage to property and infrastructure.
The storm, Cyclone Sidr, hit the southwestern coast, affecting poor fishing communities and the Sunderbans mangrove forest.
Thousands were evacuated as the cyclone approached, with the United States and Germany providing aid.
The cyclone killed at least 41 people, destroyed homes, and disrupted essential services.
Emergency relief efforts are underway, with the World Food Program providing food aid to affected victims.
The focus is on saving lives and providing essential supplies to those in need amidst the devastation.
